The Chemistry REU Leadership Group (LG) was created with the following mission objectives:


1. Communication between the REU community (current and prospective PIs) and NSF administration;


2. Assisting the REU community in meeting evolving program requirements, suggestions, and best practices;


3. Clarifying misconceptions within the community;


4. Providing information to the REU community about details of NSF funding;


5. Educating the NSF/PI community on any emerging programs (e.g., common application, common assessment, tracking, etc.);


6. Advertising opportunities to prospective REU participants;


7. Helping the REU community reach underserved undergraduate communities and meet recruiting objectives.


The LG has served as an important advocacy group for the chemistry undergraduate research community nationwide. Consistent with the broader goals of improving the REU Program, the LG maintained a two-way communication with NSF. It's primary activities were focused on (1) strengthening communication and advocacy; (2) broadening participation in the CHEM REU Program; and (3) organizing a Chemistry REU PI Workshop.


Over the course of the award, the LG:


-Hosted a virtual Chemistry REU PI Meeting in 2021


-Hosted a Mentoring Workshop at the 2019 Spring ACS Meeting entitled,


"Effective Mentoring in REU Programs."


-Recruited at National Conferences including ACS, NOBCChE via recruting booths


-Developed scripts for two webinars


-Created and utilized a LG website for dissemination of information.					Last Modified: 04/20/2024

